Reasoning: The paper discusses convolutional neural networks and their variants, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on the theoretical understanding of these networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed models, Res-CSC and MSD-CSC, involve iterative algorithms for solving sparse coding problems, which are related to optimization and numerical analysis (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the dictionary design and initialization, which are important topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the numerical experiments involve image datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia applications (cs.MM).
